#. scenario difficulty
#: po/tutorial.py:2
msgid "Tutorial"
msgstr "Didacticiel"

#. scenario author
#: po/tutorial.py:4
msgid "The UH team"
msgstr "L'équipe UH"

#. scenario description
#: po/tutorial.py:6
msgid ""
"The tutorial:\n"
"Build your first settlement and learn how to play!\n"
msgstr ""
"Didacticiel:\n"
"Établissez votre première colonie et apprenez à jouer !\n"

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:8
msgid ""
"Build a warehouse at the coast, so it is easy accessible for other ships like "
"the Free Trader."
msgstr ""
"Construisez un comptoir sur la côte, ainsi il sera facilement accessible aux "
"autres navires comme ceux du Marchand Indépendant."

#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:10
msgid "Welcome to Unknown Horizons!"
msgstr "Bienvenue dans Unknown Horizons !"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:12
msgid ""
"This is your Captain's log where all important information is stored. A short "
"notification of each task will be provided on the left of the screen."
msgstr ""
"Voici votre journal de bord où toute information importante est stockée. Un "
"court rappel de chaque tâche sera visible sur le coté gauche de l'écran."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:14
msgid ""
"If you are interested in longer descriptions, your log will hopefully provide "
"all the help you need."
msgstr ""
"Si vous voulez une plus ample description, votre journal vous fournira toute "
"l'aide dont vous aurez besoin."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:16
msgid ""
"After you close this log, it can be re-opened with the \"Captain's Log\" icon "
"in the top-right corner (below the mini-map, with a sealed document and a "
"feather)."
msgstr ""
"Après avoir fermé ce journal, il peut être réouvert avec l'icône «Journal de "
"bord» en haut à droite (sous la mini-carte, avec un document cacheté et une "
"plume)."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:18
msgid ""
"\n"
"To see your first task, click on the button \"Read next entries\" in the "
"navigation panel! It looks like this:"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Pour voir votre première tâche, cliquez le bouton «Lire entrées suivantes» "
"dans la fenêtre de navigation! Ça ressemble à ça:"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:20
msgid ""
"\n"
"For any suggestions on better wording, topics you would like to have "
"explained or even buggy conditions: Please tell us and we will try to improve "
"the tutorial!"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Pour toute suggestion sur une meilleure rédaction, une explication, ou pour "
"nous rapporter un bug : N'hésitez pas à nous contacter et nous essaierons "
"d'améliorer ce didacticiel !"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:22
msgid ""
"\n"
"Visit www.unknown-horizons.org for help on how to contact the team!"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Visitez www.unknown-horizons.org pour savoir comment contacter l'équipe !"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:24
msgid "And now, let's start the actual game."
msgstr "Et maintenant, commençons la partie."

#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:26
msgid "NEW TASK: SETTLE ON AN ISLAND"
msgstr "MISSION : COLONISER UNE ÎLE"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:28
msgid ""
"To move your ship, select it with a left click and right click on the "
"location you want it to go to."
msgstr ""
"Pour déplacer votre bateau, sélectionnez le par un clic gauche et cliquez "
"droit sur la destination de votre choix."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:30
msgid ""
"Once you are near the coast, the anchor-like button you see in the overview "
"tab will become active."
msgstr ""
"Une fois que vous êtes près de la côte, le bouton en forme d'ancre du "
"panneau deviendra actif."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:32
msgid ""
"This indicates that you are able to build a warehouse there by pressing that "
"button (called 'Build Settlement')."
msgstr ""
"Cela signifie que vous êtes alors capable de construire un comptoir ici en "
"cliquant sur ce bouton (nommé «Fonder une colonie»)."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:34
msgid ""
"Now a preview of your building is dragged around when you move the cursor."
msgstr "Maintenant, un aperçu de votre comptoir devrait suivre votre curseur."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:36
msgid ""
"You can build on any spot where this preview is not shaded red.\n"
"Click where you want to place your first building."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez construire aux endroits où cet aperçu n’apparait pas en rouge.\n"
"Cliquez à l'endroit où vous voulez placer votre première construction."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:38
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Build a warehouse at the coast."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION: Construire un comptoir sur la côte."

# I changed this to make it fit properly (seb)
#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:40
msgid "NEW TASK: BUILD A LUMBERJACK"
msgstr "MISSION : LE BÛCHERON"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:42
msgid ""
"The construction material on your ship got unloaded automatically. You can "
"now construct some basic buildings."
msgstr ""
"Les matériaux de construction de votre vaisseau sont déchargés "
"automatiquement. Vous pouvez maintenant construire quelques bâtiments "
"basiques."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:44
msgid "We will start with building a lumberjack."
msgstr "Nous commencerons par établir un bûcheron."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:46
msgid ""
"This is essential because, at this stage, boards are the only poles your "
"sailors can afford to hang their tents over."
msgstr ""
"C'est essentiel parce que, à ce niveau, les planches sont le seul matériel "
"que les marins peuvent s'offrir pour monter leurs tentes."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:48
msgid "The fisherman needs some boards to build his vessel as well."
msgstr "Le pêcheur a également besoin de planches pour construire son bateau."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:50
msgid ""
"In order to construct lumberjacks; open the build menu by either clicking the "
"big icon below the mini map or pressing B key."
msgstr ""
"Pour construire un camp de bûcheron, ouvrez le menu construction en cliquant "
"sur le grand icône sous la mini-carte, ou en pressant la touche B."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:52
msgid "The build menu is sorted by increments."
msgstr "Le menu construction est classé par niveaux."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:54
msgid ""
"You are currently in the first increment (the Sailors level) so are offered "
"only the basic buildings."
msgstr ""
"Vous êtes actuellement au premier niveau (le niveau des Marins) et donc, "
"seuls les bâtiments de bases sont accessibles."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:56
msgid ""
"\n"
"As your civilization advances, you also gain more and more complex buildings."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Plus votre civilisation avancera et plus vous pourrez construire de "
"bâtiments complexes."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:58
msgid ""
"For now, select the lumberjack under 'Companies' and build it in an area with "
"some trees around."
msgstr "Maintenant construisez un camp de bûcheron dans une zone boisée."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:60
msgid ""
"You can also plant trees later - but that costs money. Use what nature "
"provided you with!"
msgstr ""
"Vous pourrez aussi planter des arbres plus tard - mais cela vous coûtera de "
"l'argent. Utilisez ce que la nature vous offre !"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:62
msgid ""
"A company always needs a trail connection to a storage or warehouse, "
"otherwise goods will remain at the company and not be collected."
msgstr ""
"Une entreprise nécessite une route menant à un dépôt ou un comptoir, "
"autrement les biens produits y resteront et ne seront pas collectés."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:64
msgid ""
"This means that you have to build a trail connecting your warehouse (or "
"storage) and lumberjack."
msgstr ""
"Vous devez donc construire un sentier entre votre comptoir (ou votre dépôt) "
"et votre bûcheron."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:66
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Build a lumberjack in a wooded area and connect it to a road."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION: Établissez un bûcheron dans une zone boisée et connectez le à une "
"route."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:68
msgid ""
"Watch how a collector will fetch your first self-produced boards. Don't worry "
"about recruiting workers for the lumberjack. That happens automatically."
msgstr ""
"Observez comme un collecteur vat chercher vos premières planches. Ne vous "
"préoccupez pas de recruter des employers pour le bucheron. Cela se fait "
"automatiquement."

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:70
msgid "Build a lumberjack and connect it to the warehouse using a trail."
msgstr ""
"Construisez un campement de bûcheron et connectez le à votre comptoir par "
"une route."

# as upper, i put a smaller sentence here for the moment (too long)
#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:72
msgid "NEW TASK: FOOD SUPPLY"
msgstr "MISSION : LA NOURRITURE"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:74
msgid ""
"You will need to have some food-producing companies, too, because people in "
"general (and especially sailors) are very hungry."
msgstr ""
"Vous allez aussi avoir besoin d'entreprises productrices de nourriture car, "
"en générale les gens (et surtout les marins) ont toujours faim."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:76
msgid "Available companies in the first increment are the Hunter and Fisher."
msgstr "Au premier niveau vous disposez du Chasseur et du Pêcheur."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:78
msgid "The Hunter hunts animals in the forest, thus needs trees nearby."
msgstr ""
"Le chasseur chasse le gibier dans la forêt et a donc besoin de bois autour "
"de lui."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:80
msgid "Note that you can place your Hunter close to the lumberjack's forest."
msgstr "Notez que vous pouvez le placer à coté de la forêt du bûcheron."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:82
msgid ""
"It can happen that the animals don't reproduce fast enough or simply hide "
"well."
msgstr ""
"Il peut arriver que le gibier ne se reproduise pas assez rapidement ou qu'il "
"soit bien caché..."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:84
msgid ""
"Conclusion: the hunter is not too reliable if you need continuous supply."
msgstr ""
"Conclusion : le chasseur n'est pas très fiable si vous avez besoin d'un "
"approvisionnement constant."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:86
msgid ""
"\n"
"The Fisher needs a coastal building site like the warehouse and a fish school "
"in range."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Le pêcheur a besoin d'un bâtiment côtier et d'un banc de poisson à "
"proximité."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:88
msgid "He will build a small rowing vessel and catch some fish."
msgstr "Il construira un petit bateau à rame et ira attraper du poisson."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:90
msgid ""
"This is a very constant supply at the cost of a slightly longer production "
"time per unit of food."
msgstr ""
"C'est une source de nourriture très constante mais d'un temps de production "
"par unité de nourriture légèrement plus long."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:92
msgid ""
"A small settlement like yours can use both companies, and you can better "
"balance pros and cons if you see the direct comparison."
msgstr ""
"Une petite colonie comme la votre peut utiliser ces deux types "
"d'entreprises, et vous pourrez mieux en évaluer les avantages et les "
"inconvénients en les comparant directement."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:94
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Build a hunter and a fisher."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION : Construire une hutte de chasseur et une de pêcheur."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:96
msgid "Don't forget to connect them to your warehouse with trails!"
msgstr "Et n'oubliez pas les sentiers les reliant à votre comptoir !"

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:98
msgid "Build a hunter and a fisher. Connect them to the warehouse."
msgstr ""
"Construisez une cabane de chasseur et une de pêcheur. Connectez les à votre "
"comptoir."

#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:100
msgid "NEW TASK: MAIN SQUARE"
msgstr "MISSION : LA PLACE CENTRALE"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:102
msgid "Your residents need a main square where they can fetch their goods from."
msgstr ""
"Vos habitants ont besoin d'une place marchande où ils trouveront des biens "
"de consommation."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:104
msgid ""
"This means that they need a trail connection from their home to the main "
"square."
msgstr ""
"Cela signifie qu'il leur faudra un sentier menant des habitations à la place "
"centrale."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:106
msgid ""
"All goods in your warehouse are available at this 'market place', so your "
"residents do not need to walk to the fisher or even to the warehouse."
msgstr ""
"Toutes les marchandises de votre comptoir sont disponibles dans cette « "
"place du marché », donc vos habitants n'ont pas besoin d'aller chez le "
"pêcheur ou même jusqu'au comptoir."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:108
msgid ""
"You should avoid placing your main settlement tents too close to your "
"lumberjacks because building tents will clear away the trees that your "
"lumberjack needs to produce boards."
msgstr ""
"Vous devriez éviter de fonder votre campement trop prés du bucheron car les "
"tentes prennent la place du bois dont le bucheron a besion afin de produire "
"des planches."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:110
msgid ""
"Companies work without being connected to the tents, so you don't need to "
"build a road between the main square and e.g. your lumberjack tent."
msgstr ""
"Les entreprises fonctionnent sans être connectées aux tentes, donc vous "
"n'avez pas besoin de construire une route entre la place centrale et par "
"exemple la tente du bûcheron."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:112
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Build a main square."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION : Construire une place centrale."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:114
msgid ""
"\n"
"Now let's have a closer look at the main square."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Maintenant, nous allons regarder de plus près la place centrale."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:116
msgid ""
"In the 'Account' tab you get a balance sheet of this island, featuring all "
"costs you pay and all taxes you earn."
msgstr ""
"Dans l'onglet « Compte » vous obtenez un bilan de cette île, avec tous les "
"frais que vous payez ainsi que tous les impôts que vous gagnez."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:118
msgid ""
"The items 'Sale' and 'Buy' refer to your trading balance and will be "
"explained later on."
msgstr ""
"Les points « Vendre » et « Acheter » font référence à votre balance "
"commerciale et seront expliqués plus tard."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:120
msgid "If your balance is positive, you all-in-all make a profit."
msgstr "Si votre solde est positif, tout compte tenu vous faites un profit."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:122
msgid ""
"In the different increment overview tabs you can see statistics about your "
"inhabitants. You also set the increment-specific global tax here and allow or "
"deny inhabitants of this increment to upgrade to the next higher one."
msgstr ""
"Dans les différents onglets de sélection de niveaux vous pouvez voir des "
"statistiques sur vos habitants. Vous pouvez également définir le niveau "
"global de taxe spécifique et autoriser ou refuser aux habitants de ce niveau "
"de passer au niveau suivant."

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:124
msgid "Build a main square. Choose an area without many economy buildings."
msgstr ""
"Construisez une place centrale. Choisissez un endroit peu chargé en "
"bâtiments économiques."

#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:126
msgid "NEW TASK: RESIDENTIAL BUILDINGS"
msgstr "MISSION : LES HABITATIONS"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:128
msgid ""
"Settlers want to have a roof over their heads, else they won't even think of "
"living in your city! You need to provide tents."
msgstr ""
"Les colons veulent avoir un toit au dessus de la tête, autrement ils ne "
"penseront même pas à venir vivre dans votre ville ! Vous devez leurs fournir "
"des tentes."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:130
msgid ""
"Tents are the basic residential buildings. Your inhabitants will want to "
"upgrade it when they reach higher increments."
msgstr ""
"Les tentes constituent l'habitation de base. Vos habitants voudront les "
"améliorer quand ils atteindront des niveaux supérieurs."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:132
msgid ""
"Settlers may not look very useful since they will try to consume all goods "
"you produce - but they at least pay taxes, and that's the only way you can "
"make money for now!"
msgstr ""
"Les marins peuvent sembler peu ou pas très utiles dans la mesure où ils "
"essaieront de consommer tout les biens que vous produirez mais, au moins, "
"ils paient les taxes et c'est votre seule façon de gagner de l'argent pour "
"le moment."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:134
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Build a tent and connect it to the main square. Tents dont need to be "
"connected to any of the companies."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION : Construisez une tente et connectez-la à la place principale. Les "
"tentes n'ont pas besoin d'être connectées aux entreprises."

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:136
msgid "Build a tent and connect it to the main square."
msgstr "Construisez une tente et connectez-la à la place centrale."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:138
msgid ""
"\n"
"Let's have a look at the tent overview tab."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Regardons maintenant la fenêtre d'une tente."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:140
msgid ""
"You can see\n"
"* the happiness of these residents,\n"
"* the taxes they pay and\n"
"* the resources they demand."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez y voir\n"
"* la satisfaction de ses occupants,\n"
"* les taxes qu'ils paient et\n"
"* les ressources qu'ils demandent."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:142
msgid ""
"If their demands are fulfilled, happiness and thus your tax income increase."
msgstr ""
"Si vous répondez à leurs demandes, la satisfaction et donc les taxes "
"prélevées augmentent."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:144
msgid ""
"If not, happiness and income decrease. At some time your residents may get "
"really sour and simply turn their back on your village, leaving behind a "
"decaying ruin."
msgstr ""
"Sinon, la satisfaction et les rentrées d'argent diminuent. Parfois, les "
"habitants peuvent en avoir vraiment marre, ils tournent alors le dos à votre "
"village."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:146
msgid "Note that you can also change the global tax settings here, too."
msgstr "Notez que vous pouvez régler les taxes ici aussi."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:148
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Build at least three additional tents."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION: Construisez au moins 3 tentes supplémentaires."

# MAJ ou SHIFT? (Les deux sont correctes. C'est une question de gout.)
#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:150
msgid ""
"\n"
"TIP: Holding down SHIFT eases constructing multiple buildings of the same "
"kind."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"ASTUCE : Il est plus simple de construire plusieurs bâtiments du même type "
"en gardant la touche SHIFT enfoncée."

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:152
msgid ""
"Build at least three additional tents and connect them to the main square."
msgstr "Construisez 3 tentes supplémentaires et reliez les à la place centrale."

# The translation is bad, but it fits. for the moment, this is the solution
#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:154
msgid "NEW TASK: BUILD SIGNAL FIRE"
msgstr "MISSION : LA SIGNALISATION"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:156
msgid ""
"Can you see the ship passing your island from time to time? That ship belongs "
"to the Free Trader, one of the first settlers in this archipelago."
msgstr ""
"Avez-vous remarqué le navire qui passe de temps en temps devant votre île? "
"C'est le navire du marchand indépendant, l'un des premiers colons de cet "
"archipel."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:158
msgid ""
"The trader will supply your settlement with necessary goods which you can't "
"produce yet."
msgstr ""
"Il peut approvisionner votre colonie en marchandises que vous ne pouvez pas "
"encore produire."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:160
msgid ""
"You can also sell surpluses of your production, but in general consuming them "
"(by building more tents) instead of selling them yields more profit."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez également vendre vos surplus de production, mais en général il "
"est plus profitable de les consommer (en construisant plus de tentes)."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:162
msgid ""
"Normally the trader ships just sail around and look for deals, but you can "
"speed things up a bit."
msgstr ""
"Normalement les navire marchands ne font que chercher des opportunités, mais "
"vous pouvez un peu accélérer les choses."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:164
msgid ""
"For this purpose, build a signal fire at the coast near your warehouse. It "
"will show ships the way to your settlement."
msgstr ""
"À cette fin, construisez un phare sur la côte près de votre comptoir. Il "
"montrera aux navires le chemin vers votre colonie."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:166
msgid ""
"The signal fire has to cover the area which the ships pass through to catch "
"them."
msgstr ""
"Le phare doit couvrir le territoire à travers lequel les navires passent "
"pour les guider."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:168
msgid ""
"\n"
"After this little advertisment, the trader will also stop by and look into "
"your warehouse if it planned to sail past it."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Après cette annonce le marchand fera une escale chez vous pour regarder "
"votre comptoir même s'il avait prévu de passer tout droit."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:170
msgid "You can propose deals via the warehouse tab \"Buy/Sell\"."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez faire des offres dans l'onglet « Achat/Vente » de votre "
"comptoir."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:172
msgid "At the 'sailors' increment, you are equipped with three trading slots."
msgstr ""
"Au niveau « marins » vous avez trois emplacements de commerce à votre "
"disposition."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:174
msgid ""
"Click on the small icon to change the slot mode from 'Buy' to 'Sell' and vice "
"versa."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur le petit symbole pour changer le mode de « Achat » à « Vente » "
"et vice versa."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:176
msgid ""
"Click in the slot to choose the good you want to trade with. We will further "
"explain this once you are ready to trade."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur l'emplacement de commerce pour choisir la marchandise que vous "
"voulez vendre ou acheter. Nous expliquerons ce procédé plus précisément "
"lorsque vous serez prêt à faire affaire."

# 89%
#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:178
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Build a signal fire at the coast close to your warehouse."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION : Construisez un feu de signalisation sur la côte proche du "
"comptoir."

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:180
msgid "Build a signal fire at the coast close to your warehouse."
msgstr "Construisez un feu de signalisation sur la côte proche du comptoir."

# The translation is bad, but it fits. for the moment, this is the solution
#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:182
msgid "NEW TASK: LEARN TO TRADE"
msgstr "MISSION : COMMERCER"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:184
msgid ""
"Excellent! The Free Trader will now stop by at your warehouse from time to "
"time.\n"
"\n"
"Let's continue our tutorial on how to trade."
msgstr ""
"Excellent ! Le bateau-marchand va maintenant s'arrêter à votre comptoir de "
"temps en temps.\n"
"\n"
"Continuons ce tutoriel et voyons comment commercer."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:186
msgid ""
"After selecting a particular type of good, the green bar across the bottom of "
"the slot (if visible) shows you how much you have in stock of this good."
msgstr ""
"Après avoir sélectionné un type de produit, la barre verte le long de "
"l'emplacement (si visible) vous indique le niveau de stock de ce produit."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:188
msgid ""
"Dragging the slider on the right of each slot determines your 'target value' "
"which has a different meaning on 'Buy' and 'Sell'."
msgstr ""
"Bouger le curseur d'un emplacement (à droite) détermine sa « valeur cible » "
"qui a un sens différent pour « acheter » ou « vendre »."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:190
msgid ""
"When buying, you will buy sufficient to hold your 'target value' in stock."
msgstr ""
"Quand vous achetez, vous allez acheter suffisamment pour atteindre votre « "
"valeur cible » de stock."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:192
msgid ""
"When selling, the 'target value' is the stock amount at which you will always "
"stop selling until you get more of that resource again."
msgstr ""
"Quand vous vendez, la « valeur cible » est la quantité de produit que vous "
"voulez garder en réserve et ne pas vendre."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:194
msgid ""
"\n"
"For example:\n"
"Having a 'Buy' slot and 5 tons in stock, a slider positioned at 9 tons will "
"cause you to buy 4 additional tons at most."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Par exemple :\n"
"Un emplacement « achat » avec 5 tonnes en stock et un curseur à 9 provoquera "
"l'achat de 4 tonnes supplémentaires."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:196
msgid ""
"Selling works similarly. A 'Sell' slot with 18 tons in stock and the slider "
"positioned at 13 will sell up to 5 tons."
msgstr ""
"Un emplacement « vente » avec 18 tonnes en stock et un curseur à 13 vendra "
"jusqu'à 5 tonnes."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:198
msgid ""
"If the free trader however only wants to buy or sell less than your settings "
"would allow him, you need to live with that and wait for him to return."
msgstr ""
"Cependant si le bateau-marchand veut juste acheter ou vendre moins que ce "
"que vos réglages permettent, vous devrez être patient et attendre son "
"retour."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:200
msgid ""
"Unknown Horizons features smart pricing, so the value of one unit can vary.\n"
"It is NOT possible to change prices manually!"
msgstr ""
"Unknown Horizons propose un système de prix intelligent, la valeur d'une "
"unité peut donc varier.\n"
"Il n'est PAS possible de changer les prix manuellement !"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:202
msgid ""
"You can see your trade balance in the 'Account' tab comparing the 'Sale' and "
"'Buy' values there."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez voir votre balance commerciale dans l'onglet « Compte » mettant "
"en relief « Vente » et « Achat »."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:204
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Buy as many tools as you need to have 30 tools in stock!"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION : Achetez autant d'outils que nécessaire pour en avoir 30 en stock !"

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:206
msgid "Reach an island stock of at least 30 tools."
msgstr "Atteignez un stock d'au moins 30 outils."

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:208
msgid "Note that this might take a while."
msgstr "Notez que ceci peut prendre un moment."

# The translation is bad, but it fits. for the moment, this is the solution
#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:210
msgid "NEW TASK: BUILD A PAVILION"
msgstr "MISSION : LE PAVILLON"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:212
msgid "Those tools will be enough for the moment. Well done!"
msgstr "Ces outils seront suffisants pour le moment. Bien joué !"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:214
msgid "You now provide housing, a main square and food to your inhabitants."
msgstr ""
"Vous fournissez maintenant des logements, une place marchande et de la "
"nourriture à vos habitants."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:216
msgid ""
"Still there is one demand which we have not satisfied so far, you may check "
"that in the marketplace or tent tab - your sailors want a basic building "
"where they can pray."
msgstr ""
"Pourtant il y a une demande que nous ne satisfaisons pas à ce jour, vérifiez "
"le sur la fenêtre d'une tente ou de la place - vos marins veulent un "
"bâtiment où il pourront prier."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:218
msgid ""
"The solution is a pavilion which the village parson quickly puts up as "
"shelter from the sun."
msgstr ""
"La solution est un pavillon que le curé du village mettra rapidement en "
"place."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:220
msgid ""
"Service buildings like this also need to be connected to the tents with a "
"trail, else your inhabitants feel unable to reach them."
msgstr ""
"Les bâtiments de services comme celui-ci ont également besoin d'être "
"connecté aux tentes avec un sentier, autrement vos habitants seront "
"incapables de les atteindre."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:222
msgid ""
"\n"
"Note that faith is treated like a physical resource!"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Notez que la foi est traitée comme un bien physique !"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:224
msgid ""
"This means that your inhabitants need a road connection to the producer "
"(pavilion) to pick up faith there."
msgstr ""
"Cela implique que vos habitants auront besoin d'une connexion routière vers "
"le producteur (le pavillon) pour aller y chercher de la foi."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:226
msgid ""
"After some time, they will have consumed it and then again look for a "
"producer to collect more faith."
msgstr ""
"Après un certain temps, ils l'auront consommée et chercheront à nouveau un "
"producteur pour recueillir plus de foi."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:228
msgid ""
"Important:\n"
"It is NOT enough that the building is merely within a certain range of the "
"tents.\n"
"The road connection is required as well."
msgstr ""
"Attention :\n"
"Il n'est PAS suffisant que le bâtiment soit simplement dans un certain rayon "
"des tentes.\n"
"La connexion routière est également requise."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:230
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Build a pavilion with a trail to the tents in order to fulfill your "
"sailors' demand for faith."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION : Édifiez un pavillon avec un sentier vers les tentes pour qu'il "
"puisse combler la demande en foi des marins."

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:232
msgid "Build a pavilion with connection to the tents."
msgstr "Construisez un pavillon connecté aux tentes."

#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:234
msgid "NEW TASK: NEXT INCREMENT"
msgstr "MISSION : NIVEAU SUIVANT"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:236
msgid ""
"All demands are fulfilled now if your inhabitants can regularly visit the "
"main square & pavilion and your food supply is adequate."
msgstr ""
"Toutes les demandes sont maintenant remplies si vos habitants peuvent "
"visiter régulièrement la place centrale et le pavillon et que vos ressources "
"alimentaires sont suffisantes."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:238
msgid ""
"If the sailors are happy enough, they want to advance to the next increment "
"called Pioneers."
msgstr ""
"Si vos marins sont assez heureux, ils voudront avancer au prochain niveau "
"appelé Pionniers."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:240
msgid ""
"To make them happy, there is nothing else for you to do but setting taxes to "
"a lower level since you have fulfilled all the demands of your inhabitants."
msgstr ""
"Pour les rendre heureux, il n'y a rien d'autre à faire que de fixer des "
"impôts plus bas puisque vous avez répondu à toutes leurs demandes."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:242
msgid ""
"You should try to not always run on low taxes since this will probably lead "
"to bankruptcy sooner or later. For a period of time and if you know what you "
"are doing, it is fine though."
msgstr ""
"Vous devriez essayer de ne pas toujours jouer avec un niveau d'impôt trop "
"bas puisque ceci vous mènerais à la faillite tôt ou tard. Mais pour une "
"période de temps défini et si vous savez que vous faites, ce n'est pas un "
"problème."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:244
msgid ""
"After some time, the first unit should walk to the main square and have a "
"look for new construction material there to build a log house. This house "
"will replace the old tent."
msgstr ""
"Après quelques temps, un premier pionnier devrait aller à la place centrale "
"y chercher du matériel nécessaire à la construction d'une maison en rondin. "
"Cette maison remplacera la vieille tente."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:246
msgid ""
"\n"
"Such residential upgrades cost resources and can thus be restricted at the "
"main square."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"L'amélioration de l'habitat coûte des ressources et peut être limitée depuis "
"la place principale."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:248
msgid ""
"There also are upgrades of buildings without costs, as you will see with the "
"lumberjack. In this case, only the graphics change."
msgstr ""
"Comme vous pouvez l'observer chez le bucheron il existe aussi des "
"améliorations gratuites. Dans ce cas uniquement l'image du bâtiment est "
"améliorée."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:250
msgid ""
"Upgraded housing accomodates more inhabitants, and pioneers pay more taxes "
"than sailors, too."
msgstr ""
"Les logements améliorés peuvent héberger plus d'habitants et, de plus, les "
"pionniers paient plus de taxes que les marins."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:252
msgid ""
"As you may have figured out already, the downside is that pioneers demand "
"additional goods which sailors do not need - so you will need to spend this "
"extra money to make them happy as well."
msgstr ""
"Comme vous l'avez peut-être constaté, le désavantage est que les pionniers "
"demandent des biens supplémentaires dont les marins n'ont pas besoin - vous "
"devrez donc dépenser cet argent supplémentaire pour les satisfaire aussi."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:254
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Set the tax level to Low (left end) and wait for sailors to upgrade."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION : Baissez les taxes (côté gauche du régleur) et attendez que les "
"marins se développent."

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:256
msgid ""
"Set the tax level to Low (left end) and wait for your sailors to upgrade."
msgstr ""
"Réglez les taxes sur Bas (côté gauche du régleur) et attendez que vos marins "
"se développent."

#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:258
msgid "NEW TASK: BUILD A FARM"
msgstr "MISSION : CONSTRUIRE UNE FERME"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:260
msgid "Congratulations! Some of your inhabitants have reached increment II!"
msgstr ""
"Félicitations ! Certains de vos habitants ont atteint le deuxième niveau de "
"développement !"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:262
msgid ""
"Now you have access to new buildings, take a look at the Build menu again."
msgstr ""
"Vous avez maintenant accès à de nouveaux bâtiments, regardez de nouveau le "
"menu de construction."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:264
msgid "A shiny new tab appeared there."
msgstr "Un joli nouvel onglet vient d'y apparaître."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:266
msgid ""
"Pioneers will demand cloth, so you need to set up a production line for cloth "
"starting with lambs wool (which is one of the goods produced at the farm)."
msgstr ""
"Les pionniers demanderont du tissu, vous devrez créer une ligne de "
"production en commençant par la laine de mouton (l'un des biens produit à la "
"ferme)."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:268
msgid ""
"The farm is a very special production building since it can produce not only "
"one, but very many (and different) goods if you choose."
msgstr ""
"La ferme est un bâtiment de production très spéciale puisqu'elle peut "
"produire plusieurs biens (différents) si vous le voulez."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:270
msgid "The output of farms depends on what kind of fields you build around it."
msgstr ""
"La production d'une ferme dépend du type de champ que vous placez autour "
"d'elle."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:272
msgid ""
"\n"
"We will have a closer look at this later."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Nous regarderons cela de plus près plus tard."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:274
msgid ""
"Farms, like all companies producing raw materials, do not necessarily need to "
"be connected to storage or a warehouse."
msgstr ""
"Les fermes, comme tout les bâtiments produisant des biens bruts, n'ont pas "
"besoin d'être connectées à un comptoir ou au stock."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:276
msgid ""
"As long as units of the final production company can reach the farm, and "
"collectors from the warehouse or storage tent can reach the final company "
"everything's fine."
msgstr ""
"Tant qu'une personne de l'entreprise de transformation peut atteindre la "
"ferme et qu'un porteur du comptoir ou d'un dépôt peut atteindre l'entreprise "
"alors tout ira bien."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:278
msgid ""
"If you, however, plan to do some processing on different parts of the island "
"(which can make sense) or even on different islands, you will need a "
"connection to collectors."
msgstr ""
"Cependant si vous pensez affiner ces biens brut sur une autre partie de "
"l'île ou même sur une autre île, vous devrez les connecter à un dépôt ou à "
"un comptoir."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:280
msgid ""
"Try to build the farm not too close to the coast or your existing buildings "
"since it will need some space around it to work well."
msgstr ""
"Essayez de construire une ferme, mais pas trop près de la côte ou d'autres "
"bâtiments puisqu'elle aura besoin d'espace autour d'elle pour bien "
"fonctionner."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:282
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Build a farm."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION: Construire une ferme."

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:284
msgid "Build a farm and keep some empty space around it."
msgstr "Construisez une ferme et laissez de l'espace libre autour d'elle."

# The translation is bad, but it fits. for the moment, this is the solution
#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:286
msgid "NEW TASK: BUILD FIELDS"
msgstr "MISSION : LES CHAMPS"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:288
msgid "The farm itself is not going to produce anything without some fields."
msgstr "La ferme elle-même ne produira rien sans champs."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:290
msgid "You currently have the choice between pastures, potato and sugar fields."
msgstr ""
"Pour l'instant vous avez le choix entre des prés, des champs de pommes de "
"terre et des champs de canne à sucre."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:292
msgid ""
"Let's have a short overview:\n"
"* Pasture: Sheep live here, producing lamb wool.\n"
"* Potato field: Grows potatoes which are currently treated as food.\n"
"* Sugar field: Grows sugar which is used to distill liquor and (later) "
"produce confectionery."
msgstr ""
"Voyons ce qu'ils produisent :\n"
"* Prés : Des moutons vivent ici et produisent de la laine.\n"
"* Champs de pomme de terre : Des pommes de terre y poussent et constituent "
"votre nourriture.\n"
"* Champs de canne à sucre : De la canne à sucre qui sert à produire de "
"l'alcool et (plus tard) des confiseries."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:294
msgid ""
"We now only need pastures, but in case your food supply chain is too small "
"(maybe many residential buildings) you can also produce some potatoes."
msgstr ""
"Pour l'instant nous avons seulement besoin de prés mais si vos ressources "
"alimentaires ne sont pas suffisantes (beaucoup d'habitations) vous pouvez "
"aussi produire des pommes de terre."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:296
msgid ""
"Note that for potatoes you will need a road connection to the farm (not to "
"the field!) as it will be the only company to work on the goods."
msgstr ""
"Notez que dans le cas des pommes de terre vous devrez connecter la ferme "
"(pas les champs!) au réseau routier puisque c'est la seule entreprise de "
"cette chaîne de production."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:298
msgid ""
"\n"
"Make sure that all fields you build are in the area covered by the farm."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Assurez-vous que tous les champs sont dans l'espace couvert par la ferme."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:300
msgid ""
"You can have combined production - one pasture will not lead to 100 percent "
"efficiency of the farm - but you need to check how many fields one farm can "
"serve."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez combiner vos productions - un champ ne mènera pas à une "
"efficacité de 100 pour cent - mais vous devrez vérifier combien de champs la "
"ferme peut cultiver."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:302
msgid ""
"Different classes of fields require the farm units to spend more or less time "
"there (to seed, harvest, herd, etc…) and because of that, the farm may be "
"unable to serve all of the fields you built for it in time."
msgstr ""
"Les différents types de champs nécessitent plus ou moins de temps pour être "
"cultivés (planter, récolter, etc...) et à cause de cela une ferme peut ne "
"pas être en mesure de s'occuper de tous les champs à temps."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:304
msgid ""
"For now, you do not need to care about these issues a lot since you haven't "
"built any fields. Let's change that!"
msgstr ""
"Mais pour l'instant vous n'avez pas besoin de penser à ce genre de problème "
"vu que vous n'avez pas encore construit de champs. Nous devons changer cela "
"!"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:306
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Build at least one pasture in the farm's range and add potato fields if "
"you like."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION : Construisez au moins un pré dans le rayon d'action de la ferme et "
"ajoutez des champs de pommes de terre si vous le souhaitez."

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:308
msgid "Build at least one pasture and add potato fields if you like."
msgstr ""
"Construisez au moins un pré et ajoutez des champs de pommes de terre si vous "
"voulez."

#. This is a logbook page heading. Space is VERY short, please only translate to strings that fit (roughly 30 characters max).
#: po/tutorial.py:310
msgid "NEW TASK: BUILD STORAGE"
msgstr "MISSION : L'ENTREPÔT"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:312
msgid "Did you watch your lumberjack recently?"
msgstr "Avez vous observé le bûcheron récemment ?"

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:314
msgid ""
"Since your warehouse does not have unlimited space to store goods, collectors "
"will stop fetching goods from companies when stock is full."
msgstr ""
"Puisque votre comptoir n'a qu'une capacité limité, les collecteurs "
"arrêterons d'aller chercher les biens dans les entreprises lorsqu'il sera "
"plein."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:316
msgid ""
"So if no sailors recently wanted to upgrade their tents, you probably have a "
"lot of boards and in that case, the lumberjack may idle."
msgstr ""
"Donc si aucun marin n'a amélioré sa tente, vous avez probablement beaucoup "
"de planches et dans ce cas le bûcheron est peut-être inactif."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:318
msgid ""
"We can improve this situation in two different ways, and we will have a look "
"at both of them below."
msgstr ""
"Nous pouvons corriger cette situation par deux approches différentes que "
"nous allons présenter plus bas."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:320
msgid ""
"All companies offer to do no work at all.\n"
"This may sound strange, but click on the gear wheel you see in a lumberjack "
"hut's overview."
msgstr ""
"Toutes les entreprises offrent la possibilité de stopper le travail.\n"
"Cela peut paraître étrange mais essayez de cliquer sur les engrenages que "
"vous voyez, par exemple, dans le sommaire du bûcheron."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:322
msgid ""
"If this 'break' mode is enabled (we call it 'Decommissioning'), the running "
"costs you pay for the building will decrease. They won't be zero, but still "
"lower than if you keep the company producing."
msgstr ""
"Si ce mode « pause » est disponible (nous l'appelons « désaffection »), les "
"coûts de fonctionnements que vous payez pour le bâtiment baisseront. Il ne "
"baisseront pas à zéro, mais ils seront déjà plus bas que si le bâtiment "
"fonctionnait."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:324
msgid ""
"\n"
"This means that you can save money when you temporarily do not need a company "
"and do not want to tear it down, either."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Cela veut dire que vous pouvez économiser de l'argent en désactivant des "
"bâtiments que vous ne voulez pas détruire mais dont vous n'avez pas besoin "
"pour l'instant."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:326
msgid ""
"Another solution is to build the last increment-I building which has not been "
"mentioned so far: the storage tent."
msgstr ""
"Une autre solution est de construire le dernier bâtiment de niveau 1 qui n'a "
"pas encore été mentionné : l'entrepôt."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:328
msgid ""
"This building has two purposes. It:\n"
"* Offers more storage for your goods, and\n"
"* sends its own collectors to fetch goods, just like the warehouse does."
msgstr ""
"Ce bâtiment a deux fonctions. Il :\n"
"* Offre plus d'espace de stockage pour vos biens et\n"
"* Envoie ses propres collecteurs pour aller chercher des biens tout comme le "
"comptoir le fait."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:330
msgid ""
"Note that companies can also be connected to a storage in order to get their "
"products collected, and if the warehouse is overwhelmed with collector tasks, "
"you can place a storage tent to help out there."
msgstr ""
"Notez que les entreprises peuvent également être connectées à un entrepôt à "
"la place d'un comptoir et si le comptoir est surchargé vous pouvez l'aider à "
"tout collecter en construisant un entrepôt."

#. This is the text body of a logbook page.
#: po/tutorial.py:332
msgid ""
"\n"
"TASK: Build a storage tent, preferably where you need collectors."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"MISSION : Construisez un entrepôt, de préférence quelque part où vous avez "
"besoin de collecteurs."

#. This message is displayed in the widget on the left screen part. Please keep it short enough to fit there!
#: po/tutorial.py:334
msgid "Build a storage tent (increment I tab) where it makes sense."
msgstr ""
"Construisez un entrepôt (dans l'onglet niveau I) à un emplacement utile."

